Governor Nasir El-Rufai has enjoined the released abducted students of Federal College of Forestry Mechanisation, Afaka, Kaduna to see their past ordeal in the hands of abductors as a motivator to put behind and work hard towards a happier and successful future. A statement by the state Commissioner, Internal Security and Home Affairs, Samuel Aruwan, said, “Governor Nasir El-Rufai charged them to view their ordeal as a motivator to put the past behind and work hard towards a happier and successful future ahead.” The statement explained that the Kaduna State Police Command has reported to the Kaduna State Government, the release of the remaining students of the Federal College of Forestry Mechanization. According to the statement, the government rejoices with the freed students, their families and the management of the institution over this development.